The static call graph shows process_param__large has no callees (its 'callees' list is empty), so there is no path starting at process_param__large that can lead back to it. Inspecting callers (process_short_param, process_long_param) is unnecessary for detecting whether process_param__large calls itself, because recursion requires the target to initiate the call chain. Therefore no other symbols need to be provided to determine compliance with the rule.
